csharpsquidS3874-"out" and "ref" parameters should not be used"CRITICAL*cs:Ë<p>Passing a parameter by reference, which is what happens when you use the <code>out</code> or <code>ref</code> parameter modifiers, means that the
method will receive a pointer to the argument, rather than the argument itself. If the argument was a value type, the method will be able to change
the argument‚Äôs values. If it was a reference type, then the method receives a pointer to a pointer, which is usually not what was intended. Even when
it is what was intended, this is the sort of thing that‚Äôs difficult to get right, and should be used with caution.</p>
<p>This rule raises an issue when <code>out</code> or <code>ref</code> is used on a non-<code>Optional</code> parameter in a public method.
<code>Optional</code> parameters are covered by <a href='/coding_rules#rule_key=csharpsquid%3AS3447'>S3447</a>.</p>
